1288
01:07:51,276 --> 01:07:53,236
The door's open,
but you should hold back for now.

1289
01:07:53,319 --> 01:07:55,697
You're losing a lot of money this year.

1290
01:07:56,364 --> 01:07:58,116
You're not meant to be the cook.

1291
01:07:58,199 --> 01:08:00,285
-Right.
-You give orders as the owner

1292
01:08:00,368 --> 01:08:03,204
-and ask people to do the rest.
-That's right.

1293
01:08:03,288 --> 01:08:05,581
But you're blessed to have a lot of food.

1294
01:08:05,665 --> 01:08:06,916
Ah…

1295
01:08:07,000 --> 01:08:08,376
Ah…

1296
01:08:08,459 --> 01:08:09,877
That's true.

1297
01:08:09,961 --> 01:08:12,130
You'd hit it big
if you start a food-related business.

1298
01:08:12,213 --> 01:08:14,424
I've considered it for a long time.

1299
01:08:14,507 --> 01:08:18,261
And I recently got a good offer
and might go for it.

1300
01:08:18,344 --> 01:08:20,263
2025, AGED 40, PREPARING
TO START A F&B BUSINESS

1301
01:08:20,346 --> 01:08:23,850
I'm supposed to be a host,
but I'm just sitting here watching.

1302
01:08:23,933 --> 01:08:25,435
Seolhwa…

1303
01:08:26,019 --> 01:08:28,521
You know I go to see a lot of shamans.
I like her style.

1304
01:08:28,604 --> 01:08:31,065
-She just gives it to you straight.
-Very straightforward.

1305
01:08:31,774 --> 01:08:33,943
Build a foundation and start in 2028.

1306
01:08:34,027 --> 01:08:36,029
You will see actual changes

1307
01:08:36,112 --> 01:08:38,072
in 2028 for sure.

1308
01:08:38,156 --> 01:08:40,033
- In 2028.
- Yes.

1309
01:08:42,076 --> 01:08:43,619
And then…

1310
01:08:44,245 --> 01:08:45,580
In your family…

1311
01:08:46,247 --> 01:08:49,250
Neurological problems, brain issues,

1312
01:08:49,334 --> 01:08:51,169
and dementia.

1313
01:08:51,252 --> 01:08:52,378
Who has that?

1314
01:08:52,462 --> 01:08:54,756
And dementia. Who has that?

1315
01:08:59,677 --> 01:09:02,638
- My grandfather.
- Your grandfather? Huh?

1316
01:09:02,722 --> 01:09:05,641
Oh? Whoa.

1317
01:09:05,725 --> 01:09:07,310
- That info's not in here.
- No.

1318
01:09:07,393 --> 01:09:09,604
She's mentioning
so many things that are not here.

1319
01:09:09,687 --> 01:09:13,900
I'm not saying that you have
all of the health problems he has,

1320
01:09:13,983 --> 01:09:16,069
but there is a chance you might.

1321
01:09:16,152 --> 01:09:19,489
You shouldn't overwork yourself,
but rest is not written in your stars.

1322
01:09:19,572 --> 01:09:22,867
- You're never satisfied.
- Yes. That's true.

1323
01:09:22,950 --> 01:09:26,287
Yes. I know how hard he works.

1324
01:09:26,371 --> 01:09:30,291
He's very ambitious,
so he's never satisfied.

1325
01:09:31,959 --> 01:09:36,297
Your mom's life is pretty comfortable now,
so why's she so obsessed with money?

1326
01:09:40,343 --> 01:09:42,303
2015, AGED 30,
HIS MOTHER LOST ALL THEIR SAVINGS

1327
01:09:42,387 --> 01:09:44,555
That is mentioned here.

1328
01:09:46,849 --> 01:09:49,727
Your mom is always worried about

1329
01:09:49,811 --> 01:09:51,771
how to keep the family afloat.

1330
01:09:51,854 --> 01:09:53,815
- And that demoralizes your dad.
- Yes.

1331
01:09:53,898 --> 01:09:55,942
And because he's demoralized,

1332
01:09:56,025 --> 01:09:59,070
your mom's likely to take over
as the boss of the family.

1333
01:10:02,782 --> 01:10:04,742
To tell you the truth,

1334
01:10:04,826 --> 01:10:07,245
I cut contact with both my parents.

1335
01:10:07,787 --> 01:10:08,955
Oh, really?

1336
01:10:11,499 --> 01:10:12,542
Oh, dear.

1337
01:10:13,292 --> 01:10:16,170
And the reason was financial issues.

1338
01:10:16,254 --> 01:10:19,048
We had problems because of money.

1339
01:10:19,132 --> 01:10:22,635
So my mom was… Well…

1340
01:10:23,636 --> 01:10:25,471
Whenever I give her money,

1341
01:10:25,555 --> 01:10:28,224
she'd ask me for a big sum
instead of a monthly allowance.

1342
01:10:28,307 --> 01:10:30,268
She said she'd do something
with that money

1343
01:10:30,351 --> 01:10:32,103
so that I wouldn't worry about her.

1344
01:10:32,186 --> 01:10:34,856
She always asked me
for a big amount of money.

1345
01:10:34,939 --> 01:10:37,984
But when I did give her a large sum,
she ended up getting scammed.

1346
01:10:38,067 --> 01:10:40,778
And she's even made a bad investment
and lost all of the money.

1347
01:10:40,862 --> 01:10:44,866
-That's why you want a family of your own.
-Yes.

1348
01:10:44,949 --> 01:10:48,286
Yes. I think I feel lonely
around my own family.

1349
01:10:48,369 --> 01:10:50,580
So I often said on TV
that I wanted to get married,

1350
01:10:50,663 --> 01:10:52,582
and I almost got married too.

1351
01:10:53,124 --> 01:10:56,753
That's because I've always wanted
to get married since I was young.

1352
01:10:56,836 --> 01:11:00,465
I guess I thought getting married
would bring me happiness.

1353
01:11:05,052 --> 01:11:06,596
He's said that a lot.

1354
01:11:08,765 --> 01:11:10,308
He wants children too.

1355
01:11:14,812 --> 01:11:17,607
- Let me see if there's anything else.
- Okay. You're so good.

1356
01:11:17,690 --> 01:11:19,817
This is so much fun, guys.

1357
01:11:19,901 --> 01:11:22,779
- I'm so jealous.
- Hey.

1358
01:11:22,862 --> 01:11:25,031
You'll have nothing to ask Hannah, though.

1359
01:11:25,114 --> 01:11:26,199
Right.

1360
01:11:29,869 --> 01:11:31,871
The last thing my Granny spirit said is…

1361
01:11:36,042 --> 01:11:37,376
I don't know why,

1362
01:11:37,460 --> 01:11:39,879
but I've been feeling emotional
from the start.

1363
01:11:39,962 --> 01:11:41,547
We're similar people, basically.

1364
01:11:43,591 --> 01:11:47,512
I also used to be a dancer,

1365
01:11:47,595 --> 01:11:49,096
and I'm estranged from my parents.

1366
01:11:49,180 --> 01:11:51,808
I am in touch with them, but…

1367
01:11:51,891 --> 01:11:53,017
We have a lot in common.

1368
01:11:53,810 --> 01:11:56,687
- I think you chose me for a reason.
- You're right.

1369
01:11:56,771 --> 01:11:57,897
My gosh.

1370
01:11:59,148 --> 01:12:04,320
Through this show,
you got to know all the Fate Readers.

1371
01:12:04,403 --> 01:12:06,656
Don't come as a client. Come for a chat.

1372
01:12:06,739 --> 01:12:08,866
Just call us up and say,
"Hey, this happened today."

1373
01:12:08,950 --> 01:12:12,495
Since you know my situation
and can relate to it,

1374
01:12:12,578 --> 01:12:14,330
so I think talking to you would
put me at ease.

1375
01:12:16,707 --> 01:12:17,708
What…

1376
01:12:21,045 --> 01:12:22,505
Here's my number.

1377
01:12:22,588 --> 01:12:24,131
Gee, that sly…

1378
01:12:24,215 --> 01:12:26,467
Gee, that sly…

1379
01:12:27,051 --> 01:12:28,886
Now we see what your plan was.

1380
01:12:31,097 --> 01:12:33,724
Seolhwa's reading is over.

1381
01:12:34,225 --> 01:12:36,811
That was so much fun. Are you jealous?

1382
01:12:36,894 --> 01:12:37,895
So jealous.

1383
01:12:39,146 --> 01:12:41,858
Hmm. Let's not get swayed.

1384
01:12:41,941 --> 01:12:43,568
I'll just do my thing.

1385
01:12:43,651 --> 01:12:46,571
The role of a tarot master or shaman

1386
01:12:46,654 --> 01:12:51,117
is to objectively share
what they feel and see

1387
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:54,161
without letting their emotions
get the better of them.

1388
01:12:54,245 --> 01:12:56,706
So I told myself to pull myself together.

1389
01:12:56,789 --> 01:12:58,332
"Don't waver."

1390
01:12:58,416 --> 01:13:00,251
I tried not to be swayed.

1391
01:13:03,504 --> 01:13:06,090
A tarot master with prayer beads…

1392
01:13:08,593 --> 01:13:13,222
I serve Buddha, so I always wear
a necklace with 108 prayer beads

1393
01:13:13,306 --> 01:13:15,099
whenever I give a reading.

1394
01:13:17,435 --> 01:13:21,022
Choi Hannah, please begin your reading.

1395
01:13:23,107 --> 01:13:25,359
Here we go. She's started.

1396
01:13:26,193 --> 01:13:27,612
Tarot reading. Let's go.

1397
01:13:27,695 --> 01:13:28,696
Here we go.

1398
01:13:49,759 --> 01:13:51,052
She's using a different deck.

1399
01:13:52,386 --> 01:13:54,555
There are many kinds of cards.

1400
01:13:54,639 --> 01:13:58,392
Sometimes, I keep getting the same card.

1401
01:13:58,476 --> 01:14:02,521
And using just 1 deck can really limit
the range of my interpretation.

1402
01:14:06,567 --> 01:14:10,738
- Uh… I'll be blunt. Is that okay?
- Of course, it's okay.

1403
01:14:10,821 --> 01:14:12,782
Off to a great start.

1404
01:14:12,865 --> 01:14:14,450
Great. Let's go!

1405
01:14:15,159 --> 01:14:18,663
When I picked out cards
for your acquired character,

1406
01:14:18,746 --> 01:14:21,916
I got The High Priestess card.

1407
01:14:21,999 --> 01:14:25,044
You've always had a good hunch
since you were a kid.

1408
01:14:25,127 --> 01:14:27,171
And your spiritual energy made me feel

1409
01:14:27,254 --> 01:14:30,216
that you and I might be similar people.

1410
01:14:31,384 --> 01:14:33,552
When you meet someone,

1411
01:14:33,636 --> 01:14:36,764
you can tell what that person is like,

1412
01:14:36,847 --> 01:14:41,018
but you also use
your spiritual sense to tell such things.

1413
01:14:41,102 --> 01:14:43,729
He can really see things accurately.

1414
01:14:43,813 --> 01:14:47,108
He can tell at a glance
if a K-Pop idol group will make it or not.

1415
01:14:47,191 --> 01:14:48,442
He can tell?

1416
01:14:48,526 --> 01:14:50,486
- When he sees the rookies.
- For real?

1417
01:14:51,737 --> 01:14:53,572
- But because you do that,
-Yes.

1418
01:14:53,656 --> 01:14:56,701
you end up overlooking people's faults.

1419
01:14:56,784 --> 01:14:57,952
- Mmm.
- Ah…

1420
01:14:58,035 --> 01:15:00,913
That's why you feel very lonely inside.

1421
01:15:00,997 --> 01:15:03,916
The blues or sentimental thoughts

1422
01:15:04,000 --> 01:15:05,835
can take over.

1423
01:15:05,918 --> 01:15:07,378
That's what I'm getting from the cards.

1424
01:15:08,546 --> 01:15:10,548
Oh…

1425
01:15:12,883 --> 01:15:13,884
Oh…

1426
01:15:17,430 --> 01:15:18,597
How's your stomach?

1427
01:15:21,308 --> 01:15:22,810
Are you okay?

1428
01:15:22,893 --> 01:15:24,353
I have heartburn every day.

1429
01:15:24,895 --> 01:15:26,355
-It's killing me.
-Right?

1430
01:15:26,439 --> 01:15:28,274
I asked because I felt it all of a sudden.

1431
01:15:28,357 --> 01:15:29,400
Do you have acid burps?

1432
01:15:29,483 --> 01:15:31,110
- Yes.
- Acid burps.

1433
01:15:31,193 --> 01:15:34,822
I had a hard time with acid reflux.

1434
01:15:34,905 --> 01:15:37,366
Yes, it's possible
you suffer from acid burps.

1435
01:15:38,784 --> 01:15:41,746
Shamans call that "jigi."

1436
01:15:41,829 --> 01:15:45,583
I felt a sharp pain in my stomach

1437
01:15:45,666 --> 01:15:47,460
and I had acid burps.

1438
01:15:47,543 --> 01:15:49,670
I knew I was feeling his pain.

1439
01:15:51,005 --> 01:15:52,256
He has stomach issues.

1440
01:15:52,339 --> 01:15:54,467
You have serious acid reflux.

1441
01:15:54,550 --> 01:15:57,219
He'd complain about nausea too.

1442
01:15:58,387 --> 01:16:02,016
I also see so much sorrow in you.

1443
01:16:02,099 --> 01:16:05,478
But even if people try to console you,

1444
01:16:05,561 --> 01:16:08,481
it doesn't really help you feel better.

1445
01:16:10,733 --> 01:16:11,734
You're right.

1446
01:16:11,817 --> 01:16:13,569
It doesn't quite help you.

1447
01:16:13,652 --> 01:16:15,237
- It doesn't resonate with me at all.
- Mmm.

1448
01:16:15,321 --> 01:16:17,698
You believe that people don't change.

1449
01:16:17,782 --> 01:16:20,201
You think no one can change.

1450
01:16:25,164 --> 01:16:26,457
That's what I always say.

1451
01:16:29,126 --> 01:16:30,795
You strongly believe

1452
01:16:30,878 --> 01:16:32,880
that people don't change

1453
01:16:32,963 --> 01:16:35,341
and you can't fix people for the better.

1454
01:16:35,424 --> 01:16:36,425
That's spot-on.

1455
01:16:36,509 --> 01:16:40,471
You want to date and get married,

1456
01:16:40,554 --> 01:16:42,264
but you don't trust women.

1457
01:16:46,268 --> 01:16:48,020
- Seolhwa said the same thing.
- She said it too.

1458
01:16:48,104 --> 01:16:49,730
Both said he can't trust women.

1459
01:16:50,231 --> 01:16:53,609
You don't trust women.

1460
01:16:54,193 --> 01:16:57,696
Trust women first--
then talk about marriage.

1461
01:16:57,780 --> 01:16:59,115
He doesn't trust women.

1462
01:16:59,198 --> 01:17:03,035
It's because he's been hurt by people.

1463
01:17:05,287 --> 01:17:07,289
- Look at this card here.
- Okay.

1464
01:17:07,373 --> 01:17:11,001
The man's asleep
and the woman's up, doubting him.

1465
01:17:11,085 --> 01:17:12,545
- She can't go to sleep.
- Ah…

1466
01:17:12,628 --> 01:17:14,547
I'm having bad flashbacks.

1467
01:17:14,630 --> 01:17:17,341
But I do think
things will get better for you.

1468
01:17:17,424 --> 01:17:19,260
Let me see when that will be.

1469
01:17:19,343 --> 01:17:20,427
- When I'll get married?
- Yes.

1470
01:17:21,929 --> 01:17:23,931
Oh…

1471
01:17:24,014 --> 01:17:25,266
She's a love expert.

1472
01:17:25,891 --> 01:17:28,185
-A dating expert?
-Yes. She nailed it the other time too.

1473
01:17:28,269 --> 01:17:30,938
- She said that's her expertise.
- Right?

1474
01:17:32,398 --> 01:17:33,607
Hmm.

1475
01:17:34,733 --> 01:17:36,068
Your luck with marriage…

1476
01:17:38,070 --> 01:17:40,239
You will marry later in life.

1477
01:17:42,741 --> 01:17:43,909
When?

1478
01:17:43,993 --> 01:17:49,081
A woman will enter your life
when you're 43.

1479
01:17:49,165 --> 01:17:52,334
You'll consider marrying her.

1480
01:17:54,044 --> 01:17:57,256
Oh, you will have a serious relationship.

1481
01:17:59,258 --> 01:18:02,052
But I don't see this relationship
leading to a marriage.

1482
01:18:04,555 --> 01:18:05,556
No marriage?

1483
01:18:06,182 --> 01:18:08,893
Another breakup? Oh, dear.

1484
01:18:09,852 --> 01:18:12,354
- If you miss this opportunity…
- What if I do?

1485
01:18:12,438 --> 01:18:15,191
Then your next chance to marry

1486
01:18:15,274 --> 01:18:17,276
will be when you're 46 years old.

1487
01:18:17,359 --> 01:18:19,111
We got the peach tree branch,

1488
01:18:19,195 --> 01:18:21,197
so you'll be very compatible with her.

1489
01:18:21,280 --> 01:18:25,659
Sparks will fly, and things will
finally start to settle down.

1490
01:18:25,743 --> 01:18:27,328
Everything will come to an end,

1491
01:18:27,411 --> 01:18:30,706
and there will be a new beginning.

1492
01:18:30,789 --> 01:18:34,877
Can you tell the age and occupation
of the woman I'll meet when I'm 46?

1493
01:18:34,960 --> 01:18:36,837
- Of course I can. Let me see.
- For real?

1494
01:18:38,005 --> 01:18:40,174
- You can get the age and job?
- He wants to know her age.

1495
01:18:40,257 --> 01:18:42,551
It's so detailed. That's interesting.

1496
01:18:43,052 --> 01:18:45,346
-The cards tell you that too?
-Of course.

1497
01:18:45,429 --> 01:18:46,555
That's amazing.

1498
01:18:47,348 --> 01:18:48,807
Tarot's great.

1499
01:18:55,356 --> 01:18:56,857
She's a businesswoman.

1500
01:18:58,275 --> 01:18:59,818
- She runs a business?
- Yes.

1501
01:18:59,902 --> 01:19:01,320
- She's a businesswoman.
- Oh…

1502
01:19:01,403 --> 01:19:03,322
I got the King of Pentacles,
the king of money.

1503
01:19:04,490 --> 01:19:07,117
SIGNIFIES FINANCIAL STABILITY, BUSINESS

1504
01:19:07,201 --> 01:19:10,537
I sense this woman could even offer you

1505
01:19:10,621 --> 01:19:14,625
some sort of financial support to you.

1506
01:19:14,708 --> 01:19:17,753
-She's a bit younger than you.
-She's younger?

1507
01:19:17,836 --> 01:19:19,088
- My gosh.
- Wow…

1508
01:19:19,171 --> 01:19:20,589
Seolhwa said that too.

1509
01:19:21,131 --> 01:19:24,134
You need a younger woman who's mature.

1510
01:19:24,218 --> 01:19:25,970
Even a 12-year age gap is fine.

1511
01:19:26,512 --> 01:19:28,806
They're saying a lot of the same things.

1512
01:19:29,431 --> 01:19:32,184
Lastly, what kind of business should I do?

1513
01:19:32,268 --> 01:19:34,270
-Let me see.
-What field should I get into?

1514
01:19:35,771 --> 01:19:37,982
The time is up.

1515
01:19:38,065 --> 01:19:42,861
Oh, I still had a question.

1516
01:19:43,487 --> 01:19:45,531
It feels like time went by faster.

1517
01:19:45,614 --> 01:19:46,615
I know.

1518
01:19:47,324 --> 01:19:48,617
That was so much fun.

1519
01:19:50,327 --> 01:19:54,832
Seolhwa and Choi Hannah's
individual readings are over.

1520
01:19:56,000 --> 01:19:58,168
For the next 10 minutes,

1521
01:19:58,252 --> 01:20:02,673
the 2 Fate Readers
will read his fortune simultaneously.

1522
01:20:02,756 --> 01:20:05,301
THE FATE READERS READ SIMULTANEOUSLY

1523
01:20:05,384 --> 01:20:06,385
Huh?

1524
01:20:07,136 --> 01:20:09,263
They must read at the same time?

1525
01:20:09,888 --> 01:20:13,309
In front of all the other Fate Readers?

1526
01:20:13,392 --> 01:20:14,768
That's a bit ridiculous.

1527
01:20:15,894 --> 01:20:17,938
- It's a simultaneous reading.
- Oh.

1528
01:20:18,022 --> 01:20:19,481
- They're answering 1 question?
- Yes.

1529
01:20:19,565 --> 01:20:20,733
That's a bit cruel.

1530
01:20:21,358 --> 01:20:23,068
To be honest…

1531
01:20:24,445 --> 01:20:25,446
I was confident.

1532
01:20:27,531 --> 01:20:30,451
I'm bad at interrupting. What should I do?

1533
01:20:31,660 --> 01:20:33,329
I was afraid.

1534
01:20:34,330 --> 01:20:37,291
Shindong, please share your concern.

1535
01:20:38,417 --> 01:20:42,254
One of my biggest concerns is

1536
01:20:42,338 --> 01:20:45,966
something I've been thinking about
a lot recently.

1537
01:20:49,219 --> 01:20:51,764
I'm starting to wonder

1538
01:20:51,847 --> 01:20:54,975
if being a celebrity
is the right job for me long-term.

1539
01:20:55,059 --> 01:20:56,268
- It is.
- I'm unsure.

1540
01:20:57,978 --> 01:21:00,439
But as a member of SUPER JUNIOR,

1541
01:21:00,522 --> 01:21:04,485
now that I'm physically getting older,

1542
01:21:04,568 --> 01:21:06,153
- it's getting harder.
- Yes.

1543
01:21:06,236 --> 01:21:10,991
So I'm wondering how much longer
I could keep doing this.

1544
01:21:11,075 --> 01:21:12,910
Do it every now and then.

1545
01:21:13,786 --> 01:21:18,457
If there's a SUPER JUNIOR
10, 15, 20-year anniversary,

1546
01:21:18,540 --> 01:21:20,125
do that every now and then.

1547
01:21:20,209 --> 01:21:22,127
Even if I don't do it regularly,

1548
01:21:22,211 --> 01:21:24,088
- Yeah.
- I shouldn't drop it completely?

1549
01:21:24,171 --> 01:21:28,300
Yes. Your golden age is long over.

1550
01:21:29,385 --> 01:21:30,427
She's blunt.

1551
01:21:32,012 --> 01:21:33,639
Those times are long gone.

1552
01:21:34,681 --> 01:21:36,683
You will continue to be on TV.

1553
01:21:36,767 --> 01:21:38,769
But when it comes to singing and dancing,

1554
01:21:38,852 --> 01:21:40,521
you can do that on shows

1555
01:21:40,604 --> 01:21:42,981
for singers from back in the day,
every now and then.

1556
01:21:44,441 --> 01:21:46,735
-A trip down memory lane.
-Like Sugar Man.

1557
01:21:46,819 --> 01:21:48,862
It's fun to watch over a meal.

1558
01:21:50,239 --> 01:21:54,201
You're still business partners
and the SUPER JUNIOR members are around,

1559
01:21:54,284 --> 01:21:57,246
but you should cultivate
a career path of your own

1560
01:21:57,329 --> 01:21:58,997
- while continuing to be on TV.
- Right.

1561
01:22:00,332 --> 01:22:03,252
I can do just that,

1562
01:22:03,335 --> 01:22:06,588
but the problem is,
I want to continue what I've been doing.

1563
01:22:06,672 --> 01:22:08,006
You can keep going.

1564
01:22:08,090 --> 01:22:10,968
The energy that lets you continue
is currently a bit stagnant.

1565
01:22:15,514 --> 01:22:18,225
Hannah managed to interrupt me.

1566
01:22:18,308 --> 01:22:20,227
I was surprised, to be honest.

1567
01:22:22,062 --> 01:22:24,398
- She butted in pretty well.
- I know.

1568
01:22:24,481 --> 01:22:25,691
Just like that.

1569
01:22:25,774 --> 01:22:28,527
- She completely took over.
- Yes.

1570
01:22:29,278 --> 01:22:32,448
-You're meant to be in the public eye.
-Yes.

1571
01:22:32,531 --> 01:22:35,033
But you must do something else

1572
01:22:35,117 --> 01:22:36,785
to refresh your energy.

1573
01:22:36,869 --> 01:22:39,204
You must try getting into other fields

1574
01:22:39,288 --> 01:22:42,291
and you should learn to let go
when you have to.

1575
01:22:42,374 --> 01:22:45,294
You can't completely give up
your career as a singer.

1576
01:22:45,377 --> 01:22:49,298
If you do, when you watch TV,
you'll feel this helpless yearning,

1577
01:22:49,381 --> 01:22:52,342
and that could churn you up.

1578
01:22:52,426 --> 01:22:54,887
-You mentioned my members.
-Yes.

1579
01:22:54,970 --> 01:22:56,722
Out of the SUPER JUNIOR guys,

1580
01:22:56,805 --> 01:23:00,476
can you tell me who I can trust the most?

1581
01:23:01,059 --> 01:23:03,270
Oh! He can't even trust them?

1582
01:23:03,353 --> 01:23:04,980
He's seriously asking that to them?

1583
01:23:05,981 --> 01:23:08,650
- I just had a brief look.
- Okay.

1584
01:23:13,238 --> 01:23:14,948
As for your relationship with the members,

1585
01:23:15,032 --> 01:23:19,369
you seem to keep
a certain distance from them.

1586
01:23:19,453 --> 01:23:21,371
- Me?
- It's all business to you.

1587
01:23:22,331 --> 01:23:24,166
Wow, I just got the chills.

1588
01:23:25,501 --> 01:23:29,546
That's what I always tell the guys,
half joking, half serious.

1589
01:23:29,630 --> 01:23:32,257
"This is a business-based relationship."

1590
01:23:32,341 --> 01:23:34,676
"And that's how we'll last longer."

1591
01:23:34,760 --> 01:23:37,554
"We must have boundaries."
I say that often.

1592
01:23:38,055 --> 01:23:41,391
- That's true. You need boundaries.
- You do.

1593
01:23:41,475 --> 01:23:44,311
It's true. That's wise.

1594
01:23:44,394 --> 01:23:45,479
Hmm.

1595
01:23:45,562 --> 01:23:50,108
You see Heechul sometimes for work,

1596
01:23:50,192 --> 01:23:52,402
so you both stay in touch,

1597
01:23:52,486 --> 01:23:56,198
but once you think he
no longer has business ties with you,

1598
01:23:56,281 --> 01:23:57,991
you might distance yourself from him.

1599
01:23:58,075 --> 01:23:59,243
That's spot-on.

1600
01:23:59,326 --> 01:24:01,912
I might not have liked Heechul much
if he weren't popular.

1601
01:24:01,995 --> 01:24:03,705
You nailed it.

1602
01:24:03,789 --> 01:24:06,124
- My goodness.
- You nailed it.

1603
01:24:06,208 --> 01:24:08,168
- My gosh.
- Oh, dear.

1604
01:24:08,252 --> 01:24:10,045
This will cause quite a stir.

1605
01:24:10,629 --> 01:24:12,130
This is amazing.

1606
01:24:12,214 --> 01:24:14,049
Can I ask 1 last thing?

1607
01:24:14,132 --> 01:24:15,926
I was told I'd get divorced

1608
01:24:16,009 --> 01:24:19,721
if I got married before I turned 48.

1609
01:24:20,222 --> 01:24:21,807
Am I likely to get divorced?

1610
01:24:21,890 --> 01:24:23,475
Well, why am I getting this?

1611
01:24:25,060 --> 01:24:27,563
Forget this is for TV. I'll just say it.

1612
01:24:27,646 --> 01:24:31,149
The women you meet before you turn 48
all have insane temperaments.

1613
01:24:31,650 --> 01:24:32,651
Oh.

1614
01:24:32,734 --> 01:24:36,822
Your ex had the birth chart
of a celebrity, like us.

1615
01:24:36,905 --> 01:24:39,700
She is fated to sing and dance as well.

1616
01:24:39,783 --> 01:24:43,870
Your personalities were similar,
but that's also why you clashed.

1617
01:24:43,954 --> 01:24:46,498
So breaking up with her
was like a divorce of sorts.

1618
01:24:46,582 --> 01:24:48,417
- Ah. I see.
- Yeah.

1619
01:24:48,500 --> 01:24:50,460
That's true. That's very right.

1620
01:24:50,544 --> 01:24:52,504
But in your case, Shindong,

1621
01:24:52,588 --> 01:24:56,675
your acquired character
could make you consider divorce.

1622
01:24:56,758 --> 01:24:59,803
I got The Devil card
when I checked your love life.

1623
01:24:59,886 --> 01:25:00,887
Oh.

1624
01:25:00,971 --> 01:25:03,432
You must watch the timing

1625
01:25:03,515 --> 01:25:06,268
and act wisely, or you could get divorced.

1626
01:25:06,351 --> 01:25:07,978
If not divorce, it could be separation.

1627
01:25:08,061 --> 01:25:11,648
You have to focus on the person
who's with you in 2028.

1628
01:25:11,732 --> 01:25:15,485
You have to focus on the person
who's with you in 2028.

1629
01:25:15,569 --> 01:25:19,364
Even if you meet someone before then,
she might not be the one.

1630
01:25:19,448 --> 01:25:22,034
If you were to marry the woman

1631
01:25:22,117 --> 01:25:24,202
you meet before 2028,

1632
01:25:24,286 --> 01:25:27,873
nothing will actually come of it.

1633
01:25:27,956 --> 01:25:29,875
It sounds like the woman
we talked about earlier.

1634
01:25:29,958 --> 01:25:32,252
-In 2028.
-Yes, the woman you'll meet in 2 years.

1635
01:25:32,794 --> 01:25:34,963
You said 2028? Yes, I felt someone
entering your life then.

1636
01:25:35,047 --> 01:25:40,135
-How are you both saying the same thing?
-Maybe that's when your Great Luck shifts.

1637
01:25:40,218 --> 01:25:42,304
The time is up.

1638
01:25:42,387 --> 01:25:43,764
- Ah!
- That was a taster.

1639
01:25:45,557 --> 01:25:47,434
Ugh, I wanted to hear more.

1640
01:25:47,517 --> 01:25:48,810
You got 2028 with the tarot cards?

1641
01:25:48,894 --> 01:25:49,936
- Yeah.
- That's interesting.

1642
01:25:50,729 --> 01:25:52,230
The Battle of Gods.

1643
01:25:52,314 --> 01:25:54,650
The first match is over.

1644
01:25:55,400 --> 01:25:57,861
Shindong and the Fate Reapers.

1645
01:25:57,944 --> 01:26:00,530
Between Seolhwa and Choi Hannah,

1646
01:26:00,614 --> 01:26:02,491
choose the survivor.

1647
01:26:03,533 --> 01:26:05,035
How am I supposed to choose?

1648
01:26:06,703 --> 01:26:08,205
This is hard.

1649
01:26:09,373 --> 01:26:11,667
They both did so well.

1650
01:26:11,750 --> 01:26:14,002
This is a real tough one.

1651
01:26:14,086 --> 01:26:17,714
They're quite similar yet very different.

1652
01:26:17,798 --> 01:26:19,966
- Yes, that's true. Totally.
- Totally.

1653
01:26:20,050 --> 01:26:21,927
Shindong, you need to consider

1654
01:26:22,010 --> 01:26:25,681
-whose reading resonated with you more.
-Yes.

1655
01:26:25,764 --> 01:26:27,516
-We have your Book of Fate,
-Yes.

1656
01:26:27,599 --> 01:26:30,102
and we heard the readings too,
so we'll make our decisions.

1657
01:26:32,187 --> 01:26:35,399
One was sharper, and one was more vague.

1658
01:26:35,482 --> 01:26:37,109
One touched on everything,

1659
01:26:37,192 --> 01:26:39,111
while the other focused
more on love and relationships.

1660
01:26:39,194 --> 01:26:43,198
We should pick the person
who mentioned more things we didn't know.

1661
01:26:43,281 --> 01:26:45,701
The person who said stuff
that wasn't in the Book of Fate.

1662
01:26:45,784 --> 01:26:47,494
-The one who mentioned more of those.
-Yes.

1663
01:26:47,577 --> 01:26:51,081
The person who said things
he never mentioned on TV.

1664
01:26:51,164 --> 01:26:53,667
- Who is that?
- I can't tell you that.

1665
01:26:54,334 --> 01:26:56,128
This is hard. What should I do?

1666
01:27:02,676 --> 01:27:04,052
The Battle of Gods.

1667
01:27:04,803 --> 01:27:06,471
Here comes the result

1668
01:27:07,055 --> 01:27:08,056
of the first match.

1669
01:27:15,605 --> 01:27:19,276
This is the last round before the finals.

1670
01:27:19,359 --> 01:27:20,819
I want to win, to be honest.

1671
01:27:23,405 --> 01:27:24,698
I'm confident.

1672
01:27:24,781 --> 01:27:26,116
I'll be the winner today.

1673
01:27:27,993 --> 01:27:30,495
Let us reveal Shindong's choice.

1674
01:27:30,579 --> 01:27:31,872
I'm curious.

1675
01:27:33,039 --> 01:27:34,040
Who is it?

1676
01:27:34,958 --> 01:27:36,126
CHOI HANNAH

1677
01:27:40,088 --> 01:27:42,674
"Oh, I guess I did a pretty good job."

1678
01:27:42,758 --> 01:27:43,842
I was so happy.

1679
01:27:43,925 --> 01:27:45,177
I lost.

1680
01:27:46,261 --> 01:27:47,512
I thought, "Oh, I lost."

1681
01:27:49,181 --> 01:27:52,476
And now, the Fate Reapers' choice.

1682
01:27:58,607 --> 01:28:00,233
SEOLHWA

1683
01:28:00,901 --> 01:28:02,194
Huh?

1684
01:28:03,862 --> 01:28:06,281
A tie?

1685
01:28:06,364 --> 01:28:08,200
That's unexpected.

1686
01:28:08,867 --> 01:28:10,202
The Battle of Gods.

1687
01:28:10,786 --> 01:28:12,537
The first survivor is…

1688
01:28:16,082 --> 01:28:17,083
For real?

1689
01:29:12,931 --> 01:29:14,933
Translated by Jennifer Jean Lim
